.TH GENTOO-UPDATE 1 "January 2024" "gentoo-update 0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gentoo-update \- update notifier and applier for Gentoo Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gentoo-update
[\fIOPTION\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gentoo-update
is a powerful tool that assists with checking, applying, and managing
package updates on Gentoo Linux systems. It provides an interactive
workflow with pre- and post-update checks, automatic repository
synchronization, and comprehensive status monitoring.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message with usage information
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Display version and author information
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-check
Check for available package updates without applying them
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-list
List all pending package updates with versions
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-news " [\fINUM\fR]"
Display Gentoo news items. Optional \fINUM\fR specifies the number of items
to display (default: 5)
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-services
Check system services that require restart after updates
.TP
.B \-\-gen\-config
Generate a default configuration file in
.I ~/.config/gentoo-update/gentoo-update.conf
.TP
.B \-\-show\-config
Display the current configuration settings
.TP
.B \-\-edit\-config
Edit the configuration file using
.BR $EDITOR
.TP
.B \-\-tray
Start the system tray applet for background monitoring
.TP
.B \-\-tray \-\-enable
Enable automatic startup of the system tray applet
.TP
.B \-\-tray \-\-disable
Disable automatic startup of the system tray applet
.SH USAGE
.SS Default Interactive Mode
.B gentoo-update
.br
Runs the full interactive update workflow with all pre- and post-update checks
.SS Check Only
.B gentoo-update \-\-check
.br
Checks for updates and displays available packages without applying them
.SS List Updates
.B gentoo-update \-\-list
.br
Shows all pending package updates with current and new versions
.SS View News
.B gentoo-update \-\-news
.br
Displays the latest Gentoo news items
.SS Configure
.B gentoo-update \-\-gen\-config
.br
Generates a default configuration file with all available options
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file is located at
.I ~/.config/gentoo-update/gentoo-update.conf
.P
To generate a default configuration, run:
.B gentoo-update \-\-gen\-config
.P
For detailed configuration options, see
.BR gentoo-update.conf (5)
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GENTOO_UPDATE_LIBDIR
Directory containing gentoo-update libraries. If not set, the program
searches standard installation paths.
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Location of user configuration directory (default: ~/.config)
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
Location of user data directory (default: ~/.local/share)
.TP
.B HOME
User home directory
.TP
.B EDITOR
Text editor for configuration editing (default: vi)
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Invalid command-line option
.TP
.B 2
Permission denied
.TP
.B 14
Libraries directory not found
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/gentoo-update/gentoo-update.conf
User configuration file
.TP
.I /etc/gentoo-update/gentoo-update.conf
System-wide configuration (if installed)
.TP
.I /usr/share/gentoo-update/lib/*
Library files
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Check for available updates
.B gentoo-update \-c
.TP
List all pending updates
.B gentoo-update \-l
.TP
Show the last 10 news items
.B gentoo-update \-n 10
.TP
Check services requiring restart
.B gentoo-update \-s
.TP
Edit configuration
.B gentoo-update \-\-edit\-config
.TP
Generate default configuration
.B gentoo-update \-\-gen\-config
